TITLE: Resource-Based Permission Check in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Example of a resource-based permission check request using the Node.js client. The request checks if a user has edit permission on a repository within a tenant context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/api-reference/permission/check-api.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
client.permission.check({
    tenantId: "t1", 
    metadata: {
        snapToken: "",
        schemaVersion: "",
        depth: 20
    },
    entity: {
        type: "repository",
        id: "1"
    },
    permission: "edit",
    subject: {
        type: "user",
        id: "1"
    }
}).then((response) => {
    if (response.can === PermissionCheckResponse_Result.RESULT_ALLOWED) {
        console.log("RESULT_ALLOWED")
    } else {
        console.log("RESULT_DENIED")
    }
})
```

