TITLE: Creating Union-based Permission Definition in Go
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a permission definition using a union operator in Permify. It establishes a 'view' permission that is granted if the user is either in the 'viewer' relation or has 'edit' permission, showing how to build complex permission logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/docs/api-overview/permission/lookup-entity.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
SchemaBuilder{}.BuildSchema(
	entity.NewEntityDefinition(
		"document",
		[]*entity.Relation{
			entity.NewRelation("viewer", entity.EntityAndRelation{
				Entity: "user",
			}),
			entity.NewRelation("editor", entity.EntityAndRelation{
				Entity: "user",
			}),
		},
		nil,
		[]*entity.Permission{
			entity.NewPermission(
				"view",
				entity.ComputedUserset{
					Operation: entity.Operation_UNION,
					Children: []*entity.ComputedUserset{
						{
							Operand: entity.TupleToUserset{
								Tupleset: entity.TuplesetRelation{
									Relation: "viewer",
								},
								ComputedUserset: entity.ComputedUserset{
									Operand: entity.DirectUserset{},
								},
							},
						},
						{
							Operand: entity.TupleToUserset{
								Tupleset: entity.TuplesetRelation{
									Relation: "editor",
								},
								ComputedUserset: entity.ComputedUserset{
									Operand: entity.DirectUserset{},
								},
							},
						},
					},
				},
			),
		},
	),
)
```

