TITLE: Generating Authorization Token in Go for Permify API Access
DESCRIPTION: A Go function that generates an authorization token for accessing Permify APIs. The function creates and signs a JWT token with a predetermined secret using the HS256 algorithm.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/docs/getting-started/examples/notion.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func GenerateToken() string {
    token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodHS256, jwt.MapClaims{
        "exp":  time.Now().Add(time.Hour * 24).Unix(),
        "sub": "permify",
    })

    tokenString, _ := token.SignedString([]byte("permify-sample-token"))
    return tokenString
}
