TITLE: Creating Tuple Filters from API Requests in Go
DESCRIPTION: A utility method that transforms API request parameters into database filter objects for tuple queries. It handles different filter types like entity, relation, and subject filters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/docs/installation/aws.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
func (s *Service) createFilter(request interface{}) *base.TupleFilter {
	switch v := request.(type) {
	case *v1.ReadRequest:
		return &base.TupleFilter{
			Entity:   v.GetEntity(),
			Relation: v.GetRelation(),
			Subject:  v.GetSubject(),
		}
	case *v1.DeleteRequest:
		return &base.TupleFilter{
			Entity:   v.GetEntity(),
			Relation: v.GetRelation(),
			Subject:  v.GetSubject(),
		}
	default:
		return &base.TupleFilter{}
	}
}
```

