TITLE: Resolving 'After' Constraint Between Two Times in Go
DESCRIPTION: Function that determines if the first time point is after the second time point while taking into account configured temporal constraints. It applies a duration buffer when specified in the configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/docs/getting-started/modeling.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// IsAfter returns true if t1 is after t2 considering the buffer duration.
func IsAfter(t1, t2 time.Time, constraintConfigs ...types.ConstraintConfig) bool {
	config := resolveConstraintConfig(constraintConfigs)

	t1Time := t1
	t2Time := t2

	// Apply duration
	if config.AfterDuration != nil {
		t2Time = t2Time.Add(*config.AfterDuration)
	}

	return t1Time.After(t2Time)
}
```

