TITLE: Configuring and Serving Swagger UI in Go HTTP Handler
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates an HTTP handler to serve Swagger UI documentation for the Permify API. It configures middleware for CORS, sets up Swagger documentation endpoints, and handles API documentation requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/docs/use-cases.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func (s *Server) swaggerHandler() http.HandlerFunc {
	return func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
		options := middleware.SwaggerUIOpts{
			BasePath: "/api/v1",
			Path:     "/docs",
			SpecURL:  "/api/v1/swagger.json",
			Title:    "Permify API",
		}

		middleware.ServeSwaggerUI(w, r, options)
	}
}
```

