TITLE: Creating Entity with Exclusion-based Permission in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to implement an exclusion-based permission in Permify. It defines a 'view' permission that is granted to viewers of a document, except when the document is marked as private. This demonstrates implementing conditional access controls based on document attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Permify/permify/blob/master/docs/docs/api-overview/permission/lookup-entity.md#2025-04-17_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
SchemaBuilder{}.BuildSchema(
	entity.NewEntityDefinition(
		"document",
		[]*entity.Relation{
			entity.NewRelation("viewer", entity.EntityAndRelation{
				Entity: "user",
			}),
		},
		[]*entity.Attribute{
			entity.NewAttribute("private", entity.EntityAttributes_BOOLEAN),
		},
		[]*entity.Permission{
			entity.NewPermission(
				"view",
				entity.ComputedUserset{
					Operation: entity.Operation_EXCLUSION,
					Children: []*entity.ComputedUserset{
						{
							Operand: entity.TupleToUserset{
								Tupleset: entity.TuplesetRelation{
									Relation: "viewer",
								},
								ComputedUserset: entity.ComputedUserset{
									Operand: entity.DirectUserset{},
								},
							},
						},
						{
							Operand: entity.UsersetExpression{
								Operand: entity.TupleToUserset{
									Tupleset: entity.TuplesetRelation{
										Relation: "viewer",
									},
									ComputedUserset: entity.ComputedUserset{
										Operand: entity.DirectUserset{},
									},
								},
								Expression: entity.Expression{
									Attribute: "private",
									Operator: entity.Expression_EQUALS,
									BooleanValue: true,
								},
							},
						},
					},
				},
			),
		},
	),
)
```

